being annoyed.</i>

24
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,481
WATNEY: Roger that.

25
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,846
<i>Martinez, the captain
would like you to please...</i>

26
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,240
shut your smart mouth.

27
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,401
(LAUGHING)

28
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,210
We'd prefer to use
a different adjective

29
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,970
to describe Martinez's mouth.
(WATNEY LAUGHING)

30
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,765
MARTINEZ: <i>Did Beck
just insult me?</i>

31
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,922
<i>WATNEY". "Dr. Beck." And yes.</i>

32
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,606
Happy to turn the radios off
from here, Commander.

33
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,841
Just say the word.

34
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,206
<i>Went, Johanssen.</i>

35
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,566
Constant communication
is the hallmark...

36
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:08,767
Shut 'em off.

37
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,001
(BEEPS)
WATNEY: No.

38
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,321
No. Excuse me.

39
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:14,248
LEWIS: <i>I apologize
for my countrymen, Vogel.</i>

40
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,686
VOGEL: Accepted.

41
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,848
How many samples
do we need, Commander?

42
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,041
LEWIS: Seven.

43
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,646
<i>100 grams each.</i>

44
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:24,522
(ALARM BLARING)

45
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,923
We have a mission update.
A storm warning.

46
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,570
<i>Commander,
you should come inside.</i>

47
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,926
<i>You're gonna want to see this.</i>

48
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,081
What is it?

49
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,207
JOHANSSEN: <i>A</i> storm warning.

50
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,731
LEWIS: I saw that
in this morning's briefing.

51
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,769
We'll be inside
before it hits.

52
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,651
Yeah, they upgraded
their estimate.

53
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,450
The storm's gonna be
a lot worse.

54
