<i>Hello, this is Mark Watney,
astronaut.</i>

219
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:00,644
<i>I'm entering this log
for the record...</i>

220
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,567
<i>in case I don't make it.</i>

221
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:10,285
<i>It is 06:53 on Sol</i> 19...

222
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,284
<i>and I'm alive.</i>

223
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,726
<i>Obviously.</i>

224
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:18,451
<i>But I'm guessing that's gonna
come as a surprise</i>

225
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,609
<i>to my crewmates and to NASA.</i>

226
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,731
<i>And to the entire world,
really,</i> so...

227
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,245
<i>Surprise.</i>

228
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:32,961
<i>I did not die on Sol 18.</i>

229
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,804
<i>Best I can figure...</i>

230
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,327
<i>this length of our primary
communications antenna</i>

231
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,481
<i>broke off...</i>

232
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:40,842
<i>and tore through
my bio-monitor...</i>

233
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,401
<i>and ripped a hole
in me as well.</i>

234
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:47,369
<i>But the antenna
and the blood, really,</i>

235
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,488
<i>managed to seal the breach
in my suit...</i>

236
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:51,085
<i>which kept me alive,</i>

237
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,606
<i>even though the crew
must have thought I was dead.</i>

238
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,761
<i>I have no way to contact NASA.</i>

239
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:59,924
<i>And even if I could,
it's gonna be four years...</i>

240
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,441
<i>until a manned mission
can reach me.</i>

241
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:05,681
<i>And I'm in a Hab designed
to last 31 days.</i>

242
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:08,207
